<h2>How to shop safely online</h2>
<div class="card prose">
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pay with buyer protection.</strong> Use a credit card or PayPal so you can dispute a charge if something goes wrong.</li>
    <li><strong>Check the contact details.</strong> Legitimate stores list a real way to reach them — email, phone, or a physical address.</li>
    <li><strong>Read independent reviews.</strong> Look for the store on Trustpilot, Google, or Reddit rather than trusting on-site testimonials alone.</li>
    <li><strong>Be wary of prices that seem too good to be true.</strong> Steep discounts on hard-to-find items are a common lure.</li>
    <li><strong>Look for clear policies.</strong> Returns, refunds, and shipping terms should be easy to find before you buy.</li>
    <li><strong>Verify the URL.</strong> Watch for misspelled domains imitating well-known brands.</li>
  </ul>
</div>
